  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>General</Type>
    <Text>A delightful proprty that is ideal for those not wanting the direct noise of the airport yet wanting to be within very close proximity.
GH 03/09</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>SurroundingArea</Type>
    <Text>This hotel is located in the village of Copthorne. It is 6 minutes from the airport and is surrounded by green fields in a tranquil setting.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>RoomTypes</Type>
    <Text>The rooms are all of a good size, with garden views and have a traditional feel to them. There are all the facilities expected from this standard of hotel.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>PropertyInformation</Type>
    <Text>The hotel is centred around a 16th century farmhouse and the atmosphere created is very 'olde-worlde' with oak beams and log fires</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>DiningFacilities</Type>
    <Text>The restaurants are the lion d'or, which serves a formal a la carte menu.. The 'garden room' provides a more informal menu with a table d'hote menu as well as a carvery. There is also a library bar and lounge as well as a traditional English pub</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>Short</Type>
    <Text>The lobby area is very long and spacious although the ceiling is quite low. The hotel boasts a very warm atmosphere.</Text>
  </Description>
